.TH trimsec 1  "trimsec 2.4.0" 
.SH NAME
trimsec \- Speed up durations, save time, and plan your content intake.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtrimsec\fR [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-clip\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Speed up durations, save time, and plan your content intake.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-clip\fR
Use clipboard if applicable (e.g. for link)
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<COLOR>\fR [default: auto]

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
trimsec\-trim(1)
Calculate basic duration with multipliers
.TP
trimsec\-yt(1)
Calculate for YouTube videos
.TP
trimsec\-fitcheck(1)
Check whether content(s) fit in the day or a given budget of time
.TP
trimsec\-list(1)
Lists all entries in a YouTube playlist
.TP
trimsec\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v2.4.0
